Stock big nut tranny gearing. I'm guestimating that it was about 3100 rpm.
It was summertime, about 80 to 85 degrees that day.

A large portion of oil heat actually comes from the cam/lifter friction.
Higher rpm's and/or higher spring pressures will raise oil temps
signifigantly.

